claim.claim-text:
1. A method of administering medicinal fluid to a user, comprising:
delivering a medicinal fluid from a portable infusion pump system to the user according to a medicine dispensing schedule;
detecting an activity level of the user using an activity sensor positioned in the portable infusion pump system;
querying the user on a user interface of the portable infusion pump system to confirm whether the detected activity level of the user represents an actual activity level of the user; and
altering the delivery of medicinal fluid from the portable infusion pump system to a dosage different from the medicine dispensing schedule after the user confirms via the user interface that the detected activity level represents the actual activity level of the user.
